summary: This is an email chain between FBI personnel discussing logistics for interviews with potential victims of Jeffrey Epstein. The emails coordinate availability and location for victim specialists to meet with victims after interviews scheduled in West Palm Beach, Florida.

persons.name: M.S.C.J.
persons.role: Victim Specialist, Federal Bureau of Investigation
persons.context: FBI Victim Specialist based in Miami, offering to meet with Epstein victims after their interviews. Signs the email with their initials and title.

events.title: Scheduled victim interviews in West Palm Beach
events.description: The FBI Case Agent has interviews with potential Epstein victims scheduled at 11 AM and 3 PM in West Palm Beach, Florida.

events.title: Case Agent travel to Florida
events.description: The FBI Case Agent involved in the Epstein investigation travels to Florida in preparation for victim interviews.

keyFacts: FBI victim interviews with potential Epstein victims were scheduled for July 11, 2019, in West Palm Beach, Florida.
The FBI had a Victim Specialist (M.S.C.J.) based in Miami ready to provide services to victims following their interviews.
The email chain shows coordination between FBI personnel in different field offices (NY and Miami) regarding victim support logistics.
The communication emphasizes confidentiality and protection of Personally Identifiable Information (PII) under the Electronic Communication Privacy Act.
The document indicates an active FBI investigation into Epstein was ongoing in July 2019, with victim interviews being conducted.
